#Set Operations
1)Set Union
-A∪B
-A∪B={x|x∈A OR x∈B}

-Examples:
1)A={10,11,12,13} and B = {13,14,15}, then A∪B={10,11,12,13,14,15}.

2)Set Intersection
-A∩B
-A∩B={x|x∈A AND x∈B}.

-Examples:
1)A={11,12,13} and B={13,14,15}, then A∩B={13}

3)Set Difference/ Relative Complement
-A–B 
-A−B={x|x∈A AND x∉B}.

-Examples:
1)A={10,11,12,13} and B={13,14,15}, then (A−B)={10,11,12} and (B−A)={14,15}. Here, we can see (A−B)≠(B−A)

4)Complement of a Set
-A′
-A′={x|x∉A}.
-A′=(U−A) where U is a universal set.

-Examples: 
1)If A={x|x belongs to set of odd integers} then A′={y|y does not belong to set of odd integers}

5)Cartesian Product / Cross Product
-A1×A2⋯×An 

-Examples:
1)A={a,b} and B={1,2},
-A×B={(a,1),(a,2),(b,1),(b,2)}
-B×A={(1,a),(1,b),(2,a),(2,b)}

