-|P(S)|=2^4=16
-|P({∅})|=2^0=1

#Partitioning of a Set
-P1,P2,…Pn
-[Pi≠{∅} for all 0<i≤n]
-[P1∪P2∪⋯∪Pn=S]
-[Pa∩Pb={∅}, for a≠b where n≥a,b≥0]

-Examples:
-Let S={a,b,c,d,e,f,g,h}
-One probable partitioning is {a},{b,c,d},{e,f,g,h}
-Another probable partitioning is {a,b},{c,d},{e,f,g,h}

